		</table></td><td class="PanelBody" valign="Top"><table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="3" border="0" width="100%">
			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">AGRO KITING - what bards were Made to do<a name="8491"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 24 03 8:11 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>It took me a while to work this out, its pretty neat.  It is essencially soloing, with 2-5 other people.
<br />

<br />
1) GET A CASTER
<br />
You start by getting a single nuker, either a Mage or a Wizard, or a druid. (Enchanter nukes draw too much agro for some reason but they can work too if they wait longer before starting in) Clerics are ok, just have weak nukes. 
<br />

<br />
2) SIT HIM IN A SAFE PLACE
<br />
You sit your new partner in a safe spot where things don't spawn and you have a little room to run.
<br />

<br />
3) PULL/CHANT KITE
<br />
You (the bard) pull a mob to the open area and chant kite it.  At 90% a mage can send in his water pet (it has a spell that dosn't require it to be close to a mob to hit it).  At 80% the nuker can begin nuking.  As long as you keep up the quad dot's you should keep agro the entire time till the thing is dead.
<br />

<br />
4) NO SNARING
<br />
Don't let the anyone snare.  It slows the mobs and the agro goes onto the mele pets chasing them.  Then your mages have to waste mana recasting the pets.  Also it makes things tough for you if you get an add because your mobs are moving at different speeds.
<br />

<br />
5) DEALING WITH KITEABLE ADDS
<br />
If you get an add somewhere along the way that's kiteable just chant it down to 96% then switch back to your primary. That way the add dosn't randomly run after your party members who are sitting on the sidelines.  Make sure the nuker knows to stop blasting till your back on the primary so you keep agro.    
<br />

<br />
6) ENJOY (ALMOST) THE FASTEST KILL GROUPS POSSIBLE
<br />
Once you get down this techniqe with a partner adding more casters is easy.  With full groups the casters can start in earlier, like 85 or 90% without drawing agro.
<br />

<br />
Typical groups: 4 wizards, 1 mage, 1 bard
<br />
2mages, 1 wizard, 1 druid, 1 bard
<br />
1 druid, 1 mage, 1 bard, 1 wizard, 1 enchanter, 1 bard
<br />
  
<br />
Mobs die so fast that your casters won't even use much mana.  Although I did enjoy a group once where there were two bards, one to pull and the other to just sing mana song.
<br />

<br />
7) MOBS YOU CAN'T KITE
<br />
Mobs that summon or cast spells on you are not kiteable.  Mez them or just run and have your group gate.  (Since they are all casters, they can all gate).  Then regroup at same place and start over.
<br />

<br />
8) ADDITIONAL NOTES FROM MY EXPERIENCE
<br />
Wizzies and druids are easiest to work with since they understand kiting.  ( I worked with an enchater recently who said &quot;this is the most rediculous thing I've ever seen&quot; and left before she realize how great it was.  So not everyone can break out of the tank, cleric mold.)
<br />

<br />
If you group with an enchater who has had previous kiting characters, you can give them selo's and have them pull.  They can chain cast their Magic reducer spell (low mana cost, HIGH HIGH agro).  Then your casters can start nuking at 100%.  Its nuts, then you can either sing mana for the rest of your group or chant the mob as it circles.  Just remember to keep the speed on your puller. 
<br />

<br />
Hope this helps someone.
<br />
Good luck.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
