			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: AGRO KITING - what bards were Made to do<a name="8492"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 24 03 8:38 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Actually with the power of some higher level pets you can use them in place of tanks and kill stuff quite effeciently.  For instance a while back I went to PoD with some guildmates: 2 mages, one beastlord, myself and a cleric.  The beastlord would pull the mobs in, mages would sick their pets on the mob as well as the beastlords warder.  I would be out of aggro range and sing chants and slow/snare song.  We owned rcy and we were doing better than I've seen with a typical group.
<br />

<br />
Another way to do this should you be with say a wizzie or non pet type caster class is to chant kite as normal, but make sure you're casting your slow/snare song.  Now, while you're singing and avoiding the mob the wizzie can let off some nukage.  At some point the wizzie will get aggro, but with sow/selo's and snare song he/she will be able to get out of the way to let of another nuke.
<br />

<br />
As for adds I usually like to be in an area where I know I can charm things, so and add is just added dps to the current target.  If we get two adds then charm one and send it after the second add your new pet will tank mez the add while the rest of your group finishes the first mob.  By the time charm wears off you'll have quite a bit of aggro, at this point either recharm the add or if it's low enough nuke it while running the other mob about.
<br />

<br />
You have a good strategy there, these are just alternatives that I've used in these situations.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
