				<td colspan="2"><span>I tried this a long while back to no good sucess.  I had a few mages with me, for pets and nukage, and even if I chanted the mobs in PoN to 85%, they would rather rapidly turn on the mage pets.  I'm not talkin trees and such, I'm talkin the nightmares, mephits etc, and they would just tear through the mage pets like they are nothing.  If I chanted them to 70% they would not turn, but the amount of time it takes to chant those mobs to 70% is forever.
<br />

<br />
I have been in a 6 bard group before....
<br />

<br />
One would pull, and dot, and all the other bards chased the mob and meleed, and if any one of them pulled aggro, they would then become the kiter until someone else pulled aggro.  On each aggro switch each bard would take a few whacks, but with 6 bards, you can be sure that someone was singing catana, lol.  You better believe it was the most hilarious thing you would ever see, lol, and all the sparklies would make ya nuts.</span></td>
