				<td colspan="2"><span>heh when I was in the 40's I ran into a warrior that suffered from over pling, I was amazed when I could constantly pull aggro from him and he couldn't get it back even if I stopped attacking and singing.
<br />

<br />
After a while of this I finally asked him what his skills were at, no mind you this was a level 42 warrior:
<br />
Offense 50
<br />
Defense 40
<br />
1hs 90
<br />
2hs 1
<br />

<br />
Now I believe that I was like 40 or 41 at this point, and my stats were around:
<br />

<br />
Offense 190
<br />
Defense 170
<br />
1hs 198
<br />
1hb 198
<br />

<br />
And I have not ever been pl'd per say, I made my bard when Luclin came out and the hoards of people were buffing all the kitties.  That was some weird times, but the peeps I was running around with owned shadeweavers thicket for a while<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
Now, what's interesting is just the other day I was assisting a friend who just made a cleric to get some levels.  We went to good ole crushbone and found a spot.  I'd pull mobs in with chains and let my friend blast and beat on the mobs, once the mob got below 50 I'd wack it with my sword to bring it down just far enough so it wouldn't run.  My friend would heal herself up and when needed I'd group up and sing mana/regen song.
<br />

<br />
This worked out quite well, got her three levels in under an hour with the added benefit that 1hb, offense, defense, alteration, abjuration and evocation were all being worked on as well.  This is they way I have always pl'd, when a friend asks me to, since there is a heck of a lot more to pling than just levels.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=641487">Muse Ellorra Dannen</a><br>
