				<td colspan="2"><span>when there is a problem with agro, I find that slows piss mobs off more than just about anything else. (I know they piss ME off more than anything else too =)
<br />

<br />
SO... if straight DOTs are not doing the trick, we have a snare/slow(target), a slow (aoe), a Dot/slow (aoe), and higher than me a snare/slow (aoe).  I know the slows will not stack in effect, but the agro WILL stack, plus you are guaranteed to have the mob slowed at all times<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />  Gotta be awfully close for the AOEs to land, but heres the ticket... use snare/slow and 3 dots normally, and have the other 3 slows memed. (taking 7 slots total... I know I know... you can have mez, charm, or selos for true emergencies in your other slot)  Use snare and 3 dots while they nuke the bugger... *IF* you loose agro guess what, it is limping away from you, still snared, allowing you to get as close as you want to start landing all the other slows on it.  It should turn around to smack you soon enough, at which point you can dodge out of range and begin chanting again =)
<br />

<br />
I know this works fairly well from experience, but i have never tried it in precisely the way described in this thread... as I am always in a melee heavy group, with nukers a sparse comodity.  But when they get agro from me, this works... btw, for the melee groups though I don't have 3 dots, i have one dot for pulling and then self haste and group haste,  so loosing agro to the nuker can happen easier, thus the slows...<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /></span></td>
