				<td colspan="2"><span>I've always enjoyed the flexibility of a druid/bard combo.
<br />

<br />
Outdoors it is a rot fest.  I pull with dots, druid snares, then roots.  Then we both just dot it to death.
<br />

<br />
For a long time, my bard grouped with a rogue only.
<br />

<br />
And that is how we did agro kiting, I'd chant kite them to 85% or so then the rogue would just run along behind, doing dmg.  It was very fun and easy (though the rogue got dizzy a lot).
<br />

<br />
Lastnight I had a fun group, druid, shaman, necro, bard.
<br />

<br />
We did the normal root/rot fest, but the druid only did snare and root to conserve mana, the necro and shaman (having an easier time recovering mana) would just stack on whatever dots they could land.  The mobs sure didn't last long.  the best part of this was it was in a dungeon so we also got the nice exp bonuses.  the necro and myself doubled as crowd control as well.  (btw, the necro didn't use a pet.)  I don't think any of us touched a mob all night except for a few times when root wore off and they stood there snared and trying to run.  
<br />

<br />
I really think dots are much more effective than nukes when agro kiting.</span></td>
