				<td colspan="2"><span>We've got a fun little trio going on right now.  Myself, a Wizard who I group with alot, and a Necro in our guild.
<br />

<br />
I pull the mob with chants and get it down to 90% or so, the Wizard snares and roots the mob and I stand and chant it down some more, at 80% the necro tosses his dots on it.
<br />

<br />
At 70% necro sends in pet, root is usually broken and mob is now chasing me but snared, I'm still chanting while pet is chasing and meleeing, if it turns on the pet the necro tells pet to back off and I regain agro easily.
<br />

<br />
At 40% Wizard starts chain nuking till dead.
<br />

<br />
Any adds, wiz roots, necro dots.  I make it a point to run past the two of them and refresh Selo's every 2 minutes or so so if anything goes wrong everyone is Selo'd and the mobs are snared.
<br />

<br />
We've done this in a number of zones but the best exp right now, mid 50's, seems to be PoN.  I'm thinking about working in the Brusco's I got at 55 but haven't actually tried it so far.</span></td>
