				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: AGRO KITING - what bards were Made to do<a name="9861"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 6 03 7:08 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>There's quite an easy way of generating even more aggro when hunting like this =) 
<br />
Just try twisting 5 Dots on the mob of choice. I've found that while it's impossible to achieve a solid 5 song twist on normal buffing songs, it's no problem to keep 5 dots up. I believe the reason for this is, that dots only need to be present every 6 seconds (i.e. when the damage is dealt), whereas a normal buff needs to be up all the time in order to grant full bonuses. Usually, it doesnt matter if a dot wears off, after it has done its damage. 
<br />
If a mobs keeps resisting, you should get back to your 4 song twisting as you can profit from the lowered resistances when a dot has landed once. 
<br />
Even if you cant keep a real solid 5 song doting and only do damage 4 times to a mob occassionaly, it's still worth it. If I manage to keep the 5 songs up - 4 Tuyen's and Fulfil's - I have a damage increase of roughly 16% to leaving Fulfil's out.
<br />
Hope I gave you an incentive to try it =) I didn't have the idea to try it till lately, as I thought, twisting 5 songs was generally impossible...
<br />

<br />
Soundmind 52 Bard on Antonius Bayle</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
